  "prompt": "How many times in a day are the hands of a clock in straight line but opposite in direction?",
  "response": "Let's solve this step by step:\n\n1) At what positions do the hands form a straight line?\n   \u2022 When the hour and minute hands are exactly opposite each other\n   \u2022 This happens twice in one full rotation of the clock\n\n2) How often do the hands move opposite each other?\n   \u2022 The hour hand moves slowly\n   \u2022 The minute hand moves 12 times faster\n\n3) In one full day (24 hours), how many times will this happen?\n   \u2022 A day has 24 hours\n   \u2022 In one hour, the hands will be opposite each other 2 times\n   \u2022 So in 24 hours, this will happen 24 \u00d7 2 = 48 times\n\n4) Verification:\n   \u2022 This occurs every 65.45 minutes (approximately)\n   \u2022 In 12 hours: 12 \u00d7 (2) = 24 times\n   \u2022 In 24 hours: 24 \u00d7 (2) = 48 times\n\nTherefore, in a day, the hands of a clock are in a straight line but opposite in direction 48 times.\n\nThe answer is 48.",
